This paper focuses on computational models of language understanding and specifically on learning causal relations between events in narrative genres. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions experiments involving film scene descriptions, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of using newswire as a source for learning causal relations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
